section.section:
The Administration may transfer on its records the ownership of a vehicle that has been repossessed by a secured party, if the secured party submits to the Administration a certification that states:
That the secured party has a security interest in the vehicle;
That, on the basis of the security agreement or other lawful basis, the secured party has a right to the possession of and title to the vehicle;
That the secured party has possession of the vehicle; and
Any other information that the Administration requires.
